if you have a compiled caffe, you can train a model using it

Firstly, we need  generate lmdb file which is a data storage type. For image segmentation,we need images and the list of the images.Here, I put some matlab code which I used when I train models in some images gallery.
You can find the codes as follow in the archive:
  a.Divide a mixed image folder into independent folders by the image names.
  b.Divide a image folder into train and test By 9: 1 ratio.
  c.Generate a list of images in a folder or many subfolders.
  d.Upset the image list for training more effective.
  
